  "body": "Implement functionality that handles the syncing of the `preview-privacy?` setting.\r\n\r\n### Background\r\n\r\nIn `status-go` syncing of settings has been implemented, and additional setting sync *should be* a relatively straightforward process. The syncing of the `preview-privacy?` setting has been implemented from the `status-go` side.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/2478 and https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/13053\r\n\r\nHowever there is additional functionality that needs to be implemented on the `status-react` side to make `preview-privacy` work correctly.\r\n\r\nSee the QA report here [ISSUE 7: The preview-privacy setting is not applied on the synced Android device](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/13053#issuecomment-1065179963)\r\n\r\n### `status-go` Implementation\r\n\r\nCurrently the `preview-privacy` setting has its sync functionality disabled:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nPreviewPrivacy = SettingField{\r\n\treactFieldName: \"preview-privacy?\",\r\n\tdBColumnName:   \"preview_privacy\",\r\n\tvalueHandler:   BoolHandler,\r\n\t// TODO resolved issue 7 https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/13053#issuecomment-1065179963\r\n\tsyncProtobufFactory: &SyncProtobufFactory{\r\n\t\tinactive:          true, // Remove after issue is resolved\r\n\t\tfromInterface:     previewPrivacyProtobufFactory,\r\n\t\tfromStruct:        previewPrivacyProtobufFactoryStruct,\r\n\t\tvalueFromProtobuf: BoolFromSyncProtobuf,\r\n\t\tprotobufType:      protobuf.SyncSetting_PREVIEW_PRIVACY,\r\n\t},\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo reactivate the `preview-privacy` functionality in `status-go` simply remove the `inactive` field from the `SyncProtobufFactory`",
